---
// Change 20: added intro paragraph
const wins = [
  { icon: "💰", title: "$10M+ Career Sales", body: "Six years. Texas roofing. $10 million in residential and commercial jobs." },
  { icon: "📈", title: "$3.2M Best Year", body: "Multiple $1M+ months in a single year." },
  { icon: "🏆", title: "$450K First Month", body: "All-time record at Holden Roofing. Set at age 19. Still unbroken." },
  { icon: "🏢", title: "Hotels & HOAs", body: "Complex commercial projects — navigating committees, HOA groups, and high-stakes negotiations." },
  { icon: "🔄", title: "Crash → Limitless", body: "Blew out my knee. Got in a wheelchair. Built software. The injury became the company." },
  { icon: "🥇", title: "MVP & Records", body: "Training Program MVP at Priority Roofing. Highest commission-per-job record company-wide." },
];
---
<section class="site-section" id="wins">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-label">05 — The Proof</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">WINS & MILESTONES</h2>
    <p style="font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.8; opacity: 0.8; max-width: 700px; margin-bottom: 48px;">
      These aren't flex posts. They're proof that the process works — that showing up, staying consistent, and refusing to quit compounds into something real. Every number on this page has a story behind it.
    </p>
    <div class="two-col-cards">
      {wins.map((win) => (
        <div class="card tilt-card">
          <div class="card-icon">{win.icon}</div>
          <div class="card-title">{win.title}</div>
          <div class="card-body">{win.body}</div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
